#Germline risk: Observed transcriptomic score (OTRS)

This is the code to generate the observed transcriptomic risk score and assess its ability to prognosticate overall survival and progression free survival among breast cancer patients.

The observed transcriptomic score is derived from using the weight of a genes association to germline risk of breast cancer * observed expression of that gene in the tumor, summed across different thresholds of signifcance.

#OTRS-Overall survival in breast cancer

#OTRS-Progression-free survival in breast cancer

There is no statistically significant association between OS/PFS and OTRS. However, recurrence score, while not significant clinically, has the next closest statistical significance.
